BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d2-3@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261125T003000Z
DTEND:20261125T022500Z
SUMMARY:Nakamise-dori — graze for lunch
DESCRIPTION:250m of Edo-era street food + souvenir shops between Kaminarimon and Hozomon gates. Slow stroll\, graze as lunch + sweets. Mix of historic vendors + TikTok-viral picks (sweet to savory):\n\n**SWEET / SNACKS**\n1. **Asakusa Kagetsudo** — TikTok-famous jumbo melon pan\, bigger than your face\n2. **Oimoyasan Koushin** — slow-roasted yaki-imo specialist since 1876 (140+ years\; sweet potato is THE Asakusa autumn/winter street food)\n3. **Imo Pippi** — TikTok-viral crème-brûlée-style baked sweet potato with caramelized top + soft interior\n4. **Funawa** — Imo Yokan sweet potato jelly cubes (1902 institution)\n5. **Kibi dango Azuma** — Edo-era kinako-dusted rice cakes with hot drink\n6. **Asakusa Umegen** — Edo wagashi sweets since 1907 (Kintsuba\, Azuki Amanatto\, Aburi Potato)\n7. **Chinya** — Kaminari-okoshi sweet puffed rice crackers (18th-c.)\n8. **Sukeroku Honten** — Ningyo-yaki filled pancake-cakes (watch them made on the hot griddle)\n9. **Naniwa-ya** — traditional ame hard candy\n10. **Marugoto Nippon** ground floor — fresh strawberry mochi\n11. **Naruto Taiyaki Honpo** (Shin-Nakamise side branch) — fish-shaped red-bean pancake-cake\, viral on TikTok\n\n**SAVORY**\n12. **Asakusa Menchi** — beef menchi-katsu deep-fried patty (Asakusa institution)\n13. **Maguro Bito** — fresh tuna nigiri quick-bite\n14. **Curry pan** vendors throughout — crispy breaded curry bun\, often with cheese (TikTok viral)\n\nGoal: graze 5-7 stalls = full lunch. Cash-only at most. The slow-roasted sweet potato (Oimoyasan or Imo Pippi) is the late-autumn must-try.\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Nakamise-dori%20%E2%80%94%20graze%20for%20lunch%2C%2035.71237%2C139.79627
LOCATION:Asakusa Kibidango Azuma\, 1-18-1 Asakusa\, Taito
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Nakamise-dori%20%E2%80%94%20graze%20for%20lunch%2C%2035.71237%2C139.79627
GEO:35.71237;139.79627
END:VEVENT
