DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261125T043000Z
DTEND:20261125T063000Z
SUMMARY:Tokyo National Museum
DESCRIPTION:World-class Japanese art collection — samurai armor\, Buddhist sculpture\, ukiyo-e woodblock prints\, ceramics. The Honkan (main building) is the must-see — 90-120 min is plenty for the highlights. ¥1\,000pp. Bathrooms here for the day. Wed-Sun 9:30-17:00.\n~1000 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Tokyo%20National%20Museum%2C%2035.7188%2C139.7766
LOCATION:13-9 Uenokoen\, Taito-ku\, Tokyo 110-8712
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Tokyo%20National%20Museum%2C%2035.7188%2C139.7766
GEO:35.7188;139.7766
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d2-6@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261125T070000Z
DTEND:20261125T075500Z
SUMMARY:Ueno Toshogu Shrine
DESCRIPTION:Gold-leaf Edo-era shrine dedicated to Tokugawa Ieyasu\, ~5min walk SW of the National Museum. Late November = autumn foliage — red shrine + bright maple + golden ginkgo combo is the Reddit/photo-favorite shot of the trip. Walk back through Shinobazu Pond + Bentendo en route to Ameyoko. ¥500pp shrine entry.\n~500 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ueno%20Toshogu%20Shrine%2C%2035.7163%2C139.7711
LOCATION:9-88 Uenokoen\, Taito-ku\, Tokyo 110-0007
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ueno%20Toshogu%20Shrine%2C%2035.7163%2C139.7711
GEO:35.7163;139.7711
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d2-7@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261125T080000Z
DTEND:20261125T100000Z
SUMMARY:Ameyoko — post-war dinner grazing
DESCRIPTION:400m of gritty alleyway along the JR tracks between Ueno + Okachimachi stations. Survived as a post-war black market — Tokyo's real alternative to touristy Nakamise. Recently flooded with international vendors too (Turkish\, Thai\, Indian\, Korean) on top of the historic Japanese stalls. **This is the actual dinner grazing crawl.** Cash only at most\; you can politely bargain (rare in Tokyo). 20 specific picks:\n\n**JAPANESE STREET FOOD (10)**\n1. **Standing Bar Kadokura** ⭐ — signature "Ham Katsu" (thin ham in crispy breadcrumbs)\, yakitori\, udon. Open 11am.\n2. **Daitoryo** ⭐ — motsu-yaki (grilled offal) at ¥90/skewer — cult-favorite price.\n3. **Motsuyaki Daitoryo Shiten** — sister branch\, more roasted offal.\n4. **Bunraku** — yakitori + signature Shio Sour cocktail.\n5. **Yakiniku Bouya Horumonkan** ⭐ — whole-cow buying = incredible meat value. Next to Ameyoko proper.\n6. **Niku no Ohyama** ⭐ — 1932 meat wholesaler turned cheap beef bowl shop (legendary).\n7. **Hyakkaen New Fruit** ⭐ — fresh fruit sticks (pineapple\, melon\, watermelon\, strawberry) ¥100-200 each. East side of Ameyoko.\n8. **Takoyaki stalls** — octopus dumplings\, multiple vendors.\n9. **Okonomiyaki stalls** — savory grilled pancakes.\n10. **Seafood donburi stalls** — fresh sashimi-over-rice at market prices\, cheaper than Tsukiji.\n\n**INTERNATIONAL ADDITIONS (5)**\n11. **Chicken Man** — Halal-certified Turkish rotisserie + kebabs + pizza.\n12. **Xiao long bao vendors** — Chinese soup dumplings\, newer additions.\n13. **Kebab stalls** — Middle Eastern handheld.\n14. **Indian curry stalls** — recent additions.\n15. **Thai/Korean street food** — newer vendor mix.\n\n**SNACK + DEEP-FRY (5)**\n16. **Croquette + kushikatsu** — deep-fried skewers\, cheap & filling.\n17. **Oden stands** — perfect for late November chill.\n18. **Tachinomi standing-only sake spots** — ¥300-500/glass\, dive bar atmosphere.\n19. **Yakitori stalls (multiple)** — order shio (salt) first round.\n20. **¥1\,000 snack bundles** — chocolates + snacks bagged for omiyage gifts.\n\nGoal: graze 5-8 spots across 2 hours = full dinner. Budget ¥3-5K pp.\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ameyoko%20%E2%80%94%20post-war%20dinner%20grazing%2C%2035.71%2C139.7747
LOCATION:Ameyoko Shopping Street\, Ueno\, Taito-ku
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ameyoko%20%E2%80%94%20post-war%20dinner%20grazing%2C%2035.71%2C139.7747
GEO:35.71;139.7747
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d2-8@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261125T103000Z
DTEND:20261125T115500Z
SUMMARY:Omoide Yokocho — late drink stop
DESCRIPTION:Post-WWII smoke-filled yakitori alley next to Shinjuku Station\, 24 min transit from Ueno. Now that Ameyoko handled dinner\, this is just a quick 30-min atmosphere stop on the way to Golden Gai. 3 highlights worth knowing:\n\n1. **Asadachi** ⭐ — exotic horumon (frog\, salamander\, pig brain). Cult "we did the wild Tokyo thing" stop.\n2. **Kabuto** ⭐ — multi-generation charcoal eel\, every-part skewers.\n3. **Daikokuya** ⭐ — standing sake bar with 150+ Japanese sakes. Quick walk-in taste.\n\nIf still hungry: **Tsurutontan Udon** (open till morning\, the classic late-night "shime" noodle finish after drinks) or **Ichiran Ramen Shinjuku Central East** (24-hr tonkotsu backup).\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Omoide%20Yokocho%20%E2%80%94%20late%20drink%20stop%2C%2035.6936%2C139.7008
LOCATION:35.6936\,139.7008
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Omoide%20Yokocho%20%E2%80%94%20late%20drink%20stop%2C%2035.6936%2C139.7008
GEO:35.6936;139.7008
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d2-9@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261125T120000Z
DTEND:20261125T130000Z
SUMMARY:Golden Gai + Shinjuku bar map
DESCRIPTION:6 narrow alleys of 200+ micro-bars (2-8 seats each) in 1960s Showa-era buildings\, all themed by genre. **Cover charge ¥500-1500pp** at foreign-friendly bars (English signs posted on doors)\; skip ones without English signs. Drinks ¥800-1500. Don't over-stay: each bar expects you to drink + move on. Pick by VIBE\, not by checklist.\n\n**🎵 MUSIC-THEMED (Golden Gai)**\n1. **Albatross** ⭐ — antique-furniture-meets-quirky-decor\, eclectic playlist\, English speaking\, 3 floors + rooftop. Best tourist-friendly first stop.\n2. **La Jetee** — cinema-themed\, walls covered in film posters + director photos. French/Italian classics. Eponymous Chris Marker film.\n3. **Cambiare** — jazz + classical\, cocktail-forward\, foreigner-welcoming.\n4. **Hair of the Dog** — 80s punk + ska\, niche music nerd spot.\n5. **Happy Bar** — soul\, rock\, blues from "the good old days."\n6. **Bar Plastic Model** — vintage Gundam + Tamiya plastic kits on walls\, retro Showa vibe.\n7. **Araku** ⭐ — reggae + world music\, "currency wall" of foreign bills as memento.\n8. **Death Match in Hell** — heavy metal + pro wrestling theme\, kitschy Reddit cult pick.\n\n**🥃 DRINK SPECIALISTS (Golden Gai)**\n9. **Halo** — Japanese spirits only: whisky\, shochu\, awamori showcase.\n10. **Bar Kenzo** — 4-seat Japanese whisky specialist\, very intimate.\n11. **Tachibana** — traditional Japanese bar\, decades of history.\n\n**👋 ENGLISH-FRIENDLY STARTERS (Golden Gai)**\n12. **Champion / Coin Bar** ⭐ — Filipino bartenders\, sports/boxing theme\, karaoke welcome.\n13. **The Open Book** ⭐ — Alley 5 standing bar\, run by grandson of novelist Komimasa Tanaka.\n14. **Shot Bar Shadow** ⭐ — multilingual master (Arabic/German/Russian/French)\, tiny 6-seater.\n15. **Bonnie's Bar** — long-running mama-san spot\, guidebook regular.\n\n**🍸 SHINJUKU COCKTAIL DESTINATIONS (adjacent — not Golden Gai)**\nIf you want one classic-cocktail bar before or after Golden Gai\, these are world-famous:\n\n16. **Bar Ben Fiddich** ⭐⭐ — One of Asia's 50 Best Bars. 9F of an office building near Shinjuku Station. No menu — tell bartender what you want\; he prepares with mortar + pestle. Absinthe specialist with his own herb farm. **Reservations only\, day-before booking 3-6pm.**\n17. **Bar Zoetrope** ⭐ — Nishi-Shinjuku. 300+ Japanese whiskies. Dimly lit film-themed. Max 4 at a time. **The Japanese whisky shrine.**\n\n**🎷 JAZZ / LIVE MUSIC (Shinjuku)**\n18. **Shinjuku Pit Inn** — Established 1965\, legendary jazz venue with top international + Japanese musicians. Buy show ticket before going (~¥3\,500). Not a casual drop-in bar.\n\n**🤘 METAL / HEAVY ROCK (Kabukicho area\, near Golden Gai)**\n19. **Rock Bar GODZ** — Pilgrimage site for global metal community\, "bunker for audio warfare". Down narrow stairs in Kabukicho.\n20. **BAR PSY** — Small Kabukicho metal bar\, request anthems\, friendly to all.\n\nGame plan: pick 2-3 by mood. Tourist-friendly arc: **Albatross → Champion → La Jetee**. Drink-nerd arc: **Halo → Bar Kenzo → end at Zoetrope**. Wild ride: **Death Match in Hell → GODZ**.\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Golden%20Gai%20%2B%20Shinjuku%20bar%20map%2C%2035.694%2C139.705
LOCATION:35.694\,139.705
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Golden%20Gai%20%2B%20Shinjuku%20bar%20map%2C%2035.694%2C139.705
GEO:35.694;139.705
END:VEVENT
