DTEND:20261126T095500Z
SUMMARY:Higashi-Ginza pre-Kabuki dinner
DESCRIPTION:3-min walk from Kabukiza. Mid-tier ¥3-6K pp picks for the 17:30-19:15 window before 19:30 curtain:\n\n**SIT-DOWN ICONIC**\n1. **Chikuyotei Ginza** ⭐ — 1883 unagi house that caters meals to Kabukiza actors. Unagi-don ¥3-5K. No reservations — arrive 17:30 sharp.\n2. **Ginza Yondaime Takahashiya** — Kanto-style unagi (steamed then grilled)\, modern interior\, reservable.\n3. **Ginza Tonkatsu Hashikatsu / Tonkatsu Marushichi / Nishi Mura** — three old-school Higashi-Ginza tonkatsu shops. Quick turnover\, walk-in friendly.\n4. **Shari (Mitsui Garden Hotel Ginza 5-chome 2F)** — casual-but-elevated sushi/sashimi sets ¥3-5K\, easier to walk into than counter sushi.\n5. **Bergman** ⭐ — directly behind Kabukiza\; hamburg steak + Japanese beef\, ¥3\,500. **Lowest-friction pick if everything else has a line.**\n\n**KABUKIZA BASEMENT — Kobikicho Hiroba (B2)**\n6. **Izushō kintsuba** — 200-yr Iida City confection\; signature Kabukiza souvenir.\n7. **Bento counters** — pre-packed makunouchi to eat during intermission.\n8. **Café in Kobikicho Hiroba** — quick coffee + wagashi if dinner ran tight.\n\nTop 3: Chikuyotei (theme: actors eat here) → Bergman (zero-friction fallback) → grab Izushō kintsuba + an intermission bento at the basement on your way in.\n~4500 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Higashi-Ginza%20pre-Kabuki%20dinner%2C%2035.6695%2C139.767
LOCATION:Higashi-Ginza area\, Chuo-ku\, Tokyo
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Higashi-Ginza%20pre-Kabuki%20dinner%2C%2035.6695%2C139.767
GEO:35.6695;139.767
END:VEVENT
