SUMMARY:Nishiki Market
DESCRIPTION:Kyoto's Kitchen — 400m covered arcade\, ~120 shops. Most open 9:30-10:00 (verify your weekday — many close Wed). Mid-morning grazing + the trip's real knife-shopping anchor:\n\n**KNIVES (the anchor — open 9:00 sharp)**\n1. **Aritsugu** ⭐ — founded 1560 (originally swordsmiths). Free name/initial engraving on the blade. Gyuto (chef's)\, santoku (lighter)\, petty (compact for luggage)\, or the signature **hammered-copper tamagoyaki pan** (tin-lined). Get there 9:00\; engraving takes 30-45min.\n\n**SAVORY**\n2. **KAI (Kyo Saiki)** — iconic Tako Tamago (baby octopus with quail egg). KAI is the original.\n3. **Daiyasu** — oysters raw/grilled/fried\, standing counter\, locals' choice.\n4. **Nishiki Konomonoten / tsukemono stalls** — 30+ varieties of Kyoto pickles with free samples (try senmaizuki sliced turnip).\n5. **Kyoyuba Senmaruya** — fresh yuba (tofu skin) sashimi.\n6. **Toriiwaro / Torisei** — chicken skewers from Kyoto free-range birds.\n7. **Curry pan stalls** — fresh-fried curry bread (generic\, multiple).\n\n**SWEET**\n8. **Konnamonja** ⭐ — soy milk donuts + soy milk soft serve\; run by tofu shop Kyotofu Fujino. Locals love this.\n9. **Shogoin Yatsuhashi** (Nishiki branch) — cinnamon-rice triangles raw + baked.\n10. **Strawberry daifuku / ichigo mochi vendors** (seasonal).\n11. **Mochi-yaki stalls** — grilled mochi on stick.\n12. **Matcha soft serve** — multiple vendors including a Tsujiri-style.\n\nTop 3 if pressed: **Aritsugu (knife engraving) → KAI Tako Tamago → Konnamonja soy donut.**\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Nishiki%20Market%2C%2035.00497%2C135.76467
LOCATION:Nishiki-koji\, Nakagyo Ward\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Nishiki%20Market%2C%2035.00497%2C135.76467
GEO:35.00497;135.76467
END:VEVENT
