DTEND:20261202T054000Z
SUMMARY:Nakatanidou mochi pounding
DESCRIPTION:**MUST-DO SPECTACLE.** Sanjo-dori × Higashimuki intersection\, 5-min walk south of Kintetsu-Nara. Yomogi (mugwort) mochi ¥130 each\, cash only. The pounding show happens 10-15x/day (no fixed schedule — best odds noon-late afternoon\, weekends up to 30x). The video everyone has of two guys pounding mochi at superhuman speed — this is the place. Eat the mochi immediately\, it's only good warm.\n\nAfter Nakatanidou\, continue to Todai-ji (10-min walk N). **Other Nara grazing along Higashimuki arcade + Sanjo-dori:**\n- **Hiraso** — kakinoha-zushi (persimmon-leaf mackerel/salmon sushi)\, Nara classic\n- **Tanaka Honten** — alt kakinoha-zushi + Kintetsu-Nara grab-and-go bento\n- **Imanishi Honten / Yamato Shoten** — narazuke (sake-lees pickles) souvenirs\, vacuum-packed\n- **Mizuya Chaya** (Kasuga Taisha approach) — warabi mochi + kuzu mochi in a forest setting\n- **Shika senbei** — for the deer not you (¥200/pack\, photo content)\n~260 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Nakatanidou%20mochi%20pounding%2C%2034.6798%2C135.8275
LOCATION:29 Hashimotocho\, Nara 630-8217
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Nakatanidou%20mochi%20pounding%2C%2034.6798%2C135.8275
GEO:34.6798;135.8275
END:VEVENT
