SUMMARY:Otagi Nenbutsuji (1200 stone faces)
DESCRIPTION:~30 min walk uphill from bamboo grove. 1200+ rakan stone figures carved by amateur sculptors 1981–91 — each face is a different emotion: smiling\, drinking\, meditating\, laughing\, crying. Quiet\, atmospheric\, very photogenic.\n~300 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Otagi%20Nenbutsuji%20(1200%20stone%20faces)%2C%2035.0341%2C135.6646
LOCATION:2-5 Sagatoriimoto Fukatanicho\, Ukyo Ward\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Otagi%20Nenbutsuji%20(1200%20stone%20faces)%2C%2035.0341%2C135.6646
GEO:35.0341;135.6646
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d10-2b@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261203T030000Z
DTEND:20261203T035500Z
SUMMARY:Adashino Nenbutsuji (8\,000 Buddhas)
DESCRIPTION:5 min walk back down from Otagi. Thousands of small weathered stone Buddhas memorializing the forgotten dead\, plus a small bamboo grove behind the main hall. Less famous than the main Arashiyama grove — but you'll have it almost to yourselves.\n~500 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Adashino%20Nenbutsuji%20(8%2C000%20Buddhas)%2C%2035.0282%2C135.6682
LOCATION:17 Sagatoriimoto Adashinocho\, Ukyo Ward\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Adashino%20Nenbutsuji%20(8%2C000%20Buddhas)%2C%2035.0282%2C135.6682
GEO:35.0282;135.6682
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d10-2c@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261203T040000Z
DTEND:20261203T051000Z
SUMMARY:Lunch in Arashiyama town
DESCRIPTION:Walk back down toward Togetsukyo. Yudofu (tofu hot pot) is the Arashiyama signature — try Shoraian or Yudofu Sagano. Or grab matcha soba at Arashiyama Yoshimura with bridge views.\n\n**ARASHIYAMA LUNCH PICKS (mid-tier ¥1500-3000)**:\n1. **Shoraian** ⭐ — yuba/tofu kaiseki riverside with mountain view. Shofu set ¥5\,800 (yudofu + wagyu). **Reserve.** Hike up the hill.\n2. **Yudofu Sagano** — the famous one\; touristy but solid in a temple setting.\n3. **Arashiyama Yoshimura** — stone-milled soba with Togetsukyo Bridge view. Best non-tofu option.\n4. **Saga Tofu Ine** — fresh seasonal yuba + yudofu\, less crowded than Sagano.\n5. **Unagi Hirokawa** — Michelin grilled eel\, main street. Reserve.\n6. **Telacoya Honpo** (in front of Togetsukyo) — dango + senbei graze ¥200-400.\n7. **% Arabica Arashiyama** — riverside coffee\, takeout only.\n~2500 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Lunch%20in%20Arashiyama%20town%2C%2035.0148%2C135.6779
LOCATION:Arashiyama\, Ukyo Ward\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Lunch%20in%20Arashiyama%20town%2C%2035.0148%2C135.6779
GEO:35.0148;135.6779
END:VEVENT
