SUMMARY:Gekkeikan Okura Sake Museum
DESCRIPTION:Edo-era brewery from 1637\, the Japan-sake heartland. 5-min walk from Chushojima Station. Open 9:30-16:30 (last entry 16:00\, so leave Arashiyama early enough). Tasting flight at the end: 3 small cups of Gekkeikan sake + a small bottle to take home — included in ¥600 admission. The brick-and-wood riverside brewery building + canal walk between the station and museum is the real photo moment. Souvenir bottle and on-site shop if you want to buy something to take home.\n~600 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Gekkeikan%20Okura%20Sake%20Museum%2C%2034.929136%2C135.76161
LOCATION:247 Minamihama-cho\, Fushimi-ku\, Kyoto 612-8660
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Gekkeikan%20Okura%20Sake%20Museum%2C%2034.929136%2C135.76161
GEO:34.929136;135.76161
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d10-7b@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261203T090000Z
DTEND:20261203T110000Z
SUMMARY:Torisei Shijo Kiyamachi dinner
DESCRIPTION:50+ year yakitori institution\, **2-min walk from Bee's Knees speakeasy.** Fills the 5-hour Gekkeikan-to-Bee's-Knees gap with a proper dinner anchor before the late-night cocktails. ¥3-4K pp. Chicken skewers + tsukune + Kyoto-chicken sashimi. Solo or counter seating. Walk-in friendly.\n\n**ALTERNATIVES nearby Kiyamachi/Kawaramachi** if Torisei is full:\n- **Torigoro Kawaramachi** — ¥300/skewer izakaya\, all-you-can-eat option.\n- **Issen Yoshoku (Gion)** — single-menu okonomiyaki novelty\, walk-in.\n- **Honke Daiichi Asahi** (Kyoto Station) — Kyoto classic shoyu ramen\, but it's a detour.\n- **Nishiki Warai** — okonomiyaki on Nishiki arcade fringe.\n- **Weekenders Coffee Tominokoji** — pre-dinner espresso in a hidden alley (Brian-coded).\n~3500 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Torisei%20Shijo%20Kiyamachi%20dinner%2C%2035.004%2C135.77
LOCATION:Shijo-Kiyamachi area\, Nakagyo-ku\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Torisei%20Shijo%20Kiyamachi%20dinner%2C%2035.004%2C135.77
GEO:35.004;135.77
END:VEVENT
