DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261205T003000Z
DTEND:20261205T023000Z
SUMMARY:Kuromon Ichiba Market
DESCRIPTION:Uni\, wagyu\, oysters.\n\n**Heads-up:** Kuromon is now ~98% tourist (per the market itself)\, prices inflated for uni/wagyu. Graze + photo\, don't expect value. Vendor picks:\n\n**SEAFOOD**\n1. **Maguroya Kurogin** ⭐ — flagship tuna\; akami\, chu-toro\, o-toro\, kama-toro cut to order\, eat-in counter. Single must-do.\n2. **Kuromon Sanpei** — colorful uni + tuna kaisen-don bowls. The Instagram seafood-platter spot.\n3. **Grilled scallop stalls** (multiple\, ¥500-800/scallop with uni or cheese topping).\n4. **Uni shot stalls** (multiple\, ¥1000-1500 in shell).\n5. **Toyo (fugu)** — TV-famous fugu specialist (winter season\; the giant-knife guy is a longstanding market figure).\n\n**MEAT**\n6. **Maruzen Meat Shop** — Kobe + Kuroge Wagyu skewers grilled to order\, next to Maguroya Kurogin.\n7. **Nikuhoshi** — A4/A5 Matsusaka wagyu skewers.\n8. **Wagyu sushi** (multiple stalls\, blowtorched to order\, ¥500-1500/piece).\n\n**LOCALS' COUNTERWEIGHT**\n9. **Ishibashi Shokuhin** ⭐ — 50+ year family-run side-dish/pickle/lotus root stall\, rare locals' pick.\n\n**SIDES / SWEET**\n10. Eel/anago grilled-skewer stalls\; tea + pickle souvenir shops\; seasonal fresh strawberry skewers (¥500-800 amaou + condensed milk).\n\nTop 5: **Maguroya Kurogin → Maruzen wagyu → Kuromon Sanpei (photo) → Ishibashi pickle → strawberry skewer.**\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Kuromon%20Ichiba%20Market%2C%2034.6655%2C135.5066
LOCATION:34.6655\,135.5066
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Kuromon%20Ichiba%20Market%2C%2034.6655%2C135.5066
GEO:34.6655;135.5066
END:VEVENT
