DTEND:20261205T095500Z
SUMMARY:Janjan Yokocho
DESCRIPTION:Lantern alley. Map opens at the entrance arch.\n\n**SHINSEKAI KUSHIKATSU PICKS:**\n\n1. **Yaekatsu** ⭐ — 70+ years on the alley (since 1949 era)\; Reddit/locals' #1\, expect a line.\n2. **Tengu** — long-established izakaya next to Yaekatsu\; thick voluminous breading\, both locals + tourists love.\n3. **Kushikatsu Daruma Shinsekai Honten** — the 1929 mothership of the Daruma chain (different from your Day 11 Dotonbori branch).\n4. **Hatena** — lower-profile kushikatsu alternative.\n\n**SIDES TO ORDER:** Doteyaki (beef tendon + konnyaku in white miso — Shinsekai signature pairing) at any of these.\n\n**ATMOSPHERE EXTRAS:**\n- **Mihashi Shogi Club** — watch shogi games through the glass storefronts mid-alley.\n- **Standing sake/beer bars** — shoulder-to-shoulder with regulars.\n- **Smartball / pinball parlors** — vintage pachinko-ish Shinsekai specialty.\n- **Tsutenkaku Tower base** — Billiken statue: rub the feet for luck before you enter.\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Janjan%20Yokocho%2C%2034.65149%2C135.50609
LOCATION:Janjan Yokocho arcade entrance\, Naniwa\, Osaka
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Janjan%20Yokocho%2C%2034.65149%2C135.50609
GEO:34.65149;135.50609
END:VEVENT
