DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261207T223000Z
DTEND:20261208T002500Z
SUMMARY:Sushi Bun (Toyosu Market)
DESCRIPTION:**Leave Hyatt Regency by 06:30 for 07:30 arrival** (~60 min total transit). Best route: walk 8 min to Shinjuku Station → JR Yamanote Line clockwise to Shimbashi (~15 min) → **Yurikamome elevated line** to Shijo-mae Station (~15 min). Alternative: Marunouchi Line from Shinjuku-Gyoemmae to Ginza → walk to Hibiya → Toei Asakusa to Shintomicho + walk. Edomae sushi from a 150-year-old\, 5-generation chef family. Counter seating only — line forms early. Cash strongly preferred. Splurge omakase ~¥4\,500-6\,000pp.\n~4000 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Sushi%20Bun%20(Toyosu%20Market)%2C%2035.6439431%2C139.7820853
LOCATION:3F Central Seafood Wholesale Market\, 6-5-1 Toyosu\, Koto-ku\, Tokyo 135-0061
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Sushi%20Bun%20(Toyosu%20Market)%2C%2035.6439431%2C139.7820853
GEO:35.6439431;139.7820853
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d15-0a@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261208T003000Z
DTEND:20261208T012500Z
SUMMARY:Tsukiji Outer Market
DESCRIPTION:Note: Tsukiji is 3km NW of Toyosu — ~10-15 min via Yurikamome from Shijo-mae or taxi. Tsukiji Outer Market is still the fun grazing area — knife shops (Aritsugu\, Sugimoto)\, tamagoyaki on a stick\, sea urchin shots\, grilled scallops\, matcha mochi. After the Sushi Bun breakfast\, this is the food-bazaar wandering before heading to Ginza.\n\n**TSUKIJI VENDOR PICKS** (touristy but still has the goods):\n\n**SUSHI / SASHIMI**\n1. **Tsukiji Itadori Bekkan** — chirashi/kaisendon made to order\, most-recommended sit-down.\n2. **Tsukiji Itadori Uogashi Senryo** — hitsumabushi-style seafood bowl three ways\, less touristy.\n3. **Maguro skewer stands along Monzeki-dori** — fresh otoro on a stick.\n\n**TAMAGOYAKI + SWEET**\n4. **Marutake** ⭐ — slightly sweet rolled egg\, sumo-wrestler favorite.\n5. **Yamacho** — ¥100 skewered tamago\, caramelized exterior\, dessert-sweet\, long queue.\n6. **Tsukiji Shouro** — saltier savory tamagoyaki\, the third major specialist.\n7. **Tsukiji Sanokiya** — tuna-shaped taiyaki (custard or anko).\n\n**GRILLED**\n8. **Marutake Suisan** — grilled jumbo scallop butter+soy\, fresh oysters.\n9. **Wagyu+uni skewers** (multiple stalls) — A5 sticks\, tourist-priced (~¥1500+) but iconic.\n10. **Kitsuneya** ⭐ — open-air corner with bubbling cauldron of gyu-motsu-ni (beef offal stew over rice)\; legit locals' breakfast spot.\n\n**KNIVES (the trip's second knife shopping anchor)**\n11. **Aritsugu Tsukiji** — same lineage as Nishiki (founded 1560)\, engraving while you wait.\n12. **Sugimoto Hamono** — Chinese-cleaver and pro-chef knives.\n13. **Tsukiji Masamoto** — classic yanagiba.\n14. **Bonito flake / katsuobushi shops** (Wadakyu et al.) — freshly shaved\, vacuum-packed for travel.\n\nTop 3 picks for 90-min window: **Marutake or Yamacho tamagoyaki → Kitsuneya motsu-ni OR butter-soy scallop → Aritsugu engraved knife.** Skip the wagyu+uni sticks (tourist photo bait) and sit-down sushi counters (queue eats your morning).\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Tsukiji%20Outer%20Market%2C%2035.6655%2C139.7707
LOCATION:Tsukiji Outer Market\, 4 Chome Tsukiji\, Chuo City
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Tsukiji%20Outer%20Market%2C%2035.6655%2C139.7707
GEO:35.6655;139.7707
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d15-0c@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260715T020241Z
DTSTART:20261208T013000Z
DTEND:20261208T022500Z
SUMMARY:Hamarikyu Gardens + Nakajima Teahouse
DESCRIPTION:10-min walk from Tsukiji Outer Market. Shogun's seaside hunting garden — Edo-era stroll garden with a tidal pond and Nakajima Teahouse on stilts mid-pond. ¥300 entry + ~¥850 matcha + namagashi at the teahouse (sit-down\, ~30 min). Late-November maples + ginkgos at peak. The most photogenic skyscraper-backdrop-meets-Edo-garden moment in central Tokyo. Daily 9:00–17:00 (last entry 16:30).\n~1200 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Hamarikyu%20Gardens%20%2B%20Nakajima%20Teahouse%2C%2035.6601%2C139.7634
LOCATION:1-1 Hama-Rikyu-Teien\, Chuo City\, Tokyo
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Hamarikyu%20Gardens%20%2B%20Nakajima%20Teahouse%2C%2035.6601%2C139.7634
GEO:35.6601;139.7634
END:VEVENT
